properties.name: Skopje
properties.quote: At the Bulgaria-Yugoslavia border I decided that the Danube was too tame.��� I wanted a new river to conquer, and just a short distance across country lay the Vardar River, which had never been navigated.��� Those upper reaches of the Vardar proved savage.���The river plunges through steep mountains, with a succession of fierce rapids waiting to hurl the canoeist onwards and downwards through the gorges. I reached Veles, in Macedonia, with half the kayak's ribs broken.���

properties.name: Veles
properties.quote: Then the Vardar froze over solid.��� Altogether, I was delayed five months in Veles.��� It was spring when I finally got away.���

properties.name: Macedonian-Greek border
properties.quote: I crossed the Macedonian-Greek border?Around midnight I was awakened by shouting, and I pulled back the flap of my tent to find myself looking into two carbines, held by two frontier guards.  ?  We shared no language, so I showed them my passport.  After muttering over it for a while, one guard signed to me to mount the second guard's horse?He was a charming young officer.  Directly he saw the Greek visa on my passport, he offered profuse apologies, and followed this by insisting that I should come into his room and drink coffee and wine.

properties.name: Salonika (Thessaloniki)
properties.desc: Thessaloniki, Municipality of Thessaloniki, Macedonia - Thrace Administration, Greece
properties.quote: At Salonika I faced the sea at last.��� With few incidents, my voyage down the coast of Greece was a kayakist's dream, and at last I was beaching my kayak at Andros.���

properties.name: Andros
properties.desc: Dimos Androu, Aegean Sea Administration, Greece
properties.quote: I was scarcely ashore when two little Greek girls in white Sunday dresses came across the sand towards me, carrying a round loaf of bread with three colored eggs sticking out of it.��� So it was Easter Day, and this was Andros' welcome!

properties.name: Famagusta
properties.desc: Famagusta, Famagusta, Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus

properties.name: Aleppo
properties.quote: After crossing to Syria I travelled by bus to Aleppo and from there via Mescene down the Euphrates, across Syria and Iraq and into the Shatt el Arab.

properties.name: Meskene (Maskanah)
properties.quote: Since the kayak would have to be freighted either way, I decided that Suez offered a too well-beaten path-why not land on the Syrian coast and take the bus to Meskene?That would be something!

properties.name: Basrah
properties.quote: My legs blue with cold, I arrived at Basra on the second day of Christmas

properties.name: Bushehr
properties.quote: From Basra to Bushir would have taken me a journey time of eight days under normal circumstances, but because of heavy sea I needed 35 days. I was forced to wait on an empty island for an opportunity to carry on for seven days, although I barely had enough provisions for four days. The only company I had was from a half rotten corpse that had been carried through the cliffs, and the stench was unbearable.

properties.name: Gwadar
properties.quote: In Baluchistan my canoe had become too damaged to carry on seafaring. Nobody could believe that I had reached the harbour with that vessel. I repaired it by the book.

properties.name: Mandvi
properties.quote: Another part of my journey was the ride from Karachi to Kutch Mandvi in the last days of January. I had nothing to eat and lived off oysters that I could catch. It was oysters for breakfast, oysters for lunch and oysters for dinner.

properties.name: Porbandar
properties.quote: When I rode along the Porbandar coast, shaken by malaria and without having slept for days, I capsized in the surf for the first time. But I managed to get to shore and found admission to the hospital of the Maharajah of Porbandar and was treated for malaria by his personal physician.

properties.name: Gulf of Khambhat
properties.quote: In the Gulf of Khambhat, I was arrested as a spy for two days. They believed of my canoe that it could be used equally as a submarine and an aeroplane and thus be perfectly adequate for spying.

properties.name: Surat
properties.quote: Released with clemency, I crossed the Gulf of Khambhat to Surat, where a tidal range of 35 feet produces the most difficult water conditions.

properties.name: Vengurka (Vengurla)
properties.quote: Then I paddled on to Goa and Mangalore, where I capsized the second time and lost my entire equipment.

properties.name: Adam's Bridge (Rama's Bridge or Rama Setu)
properties.desc: Adam's Bridge (Rama's Bridge or Rama Setu) coast of Tamil Nadu, India

properties.name: Puttalam
properties.desc: Puttalam, Puttalam District, North Western Province, Sri Lanka
properties.quote: Here and there I tried using inland waterways but was stopped time and again by abounding masses of people who wished to see the crazy German who lived off pills and travelled in a boat which, as was reported, could dive and fly. So I kept coming back out onto the clear, if more dangerous, open ocean.

properties.name: Galle
properties.quote: I have been in Ceylon for three months now and find it extraordinarily beautiful. Next Sunday I will leave Ceylon and attempt to reach Australia in maybe... three years. Half of my journey is over. I've had wonderful experiences and although it was difficult in the beginning, with growing success I found my task considerably easier.

properties.name: Cuddalore
properties.desc: Cuddalore, Duccalore district, Tamil Nadu, India
properties.quote: The surf was very difficult in these parts. From Cuddalore I came straight ? had to come straight on 90 miles in 26 hours.��� That is not however the longest I have done.��� I did 92 miles, not along the coast, but across the sea and it took me 48 hours. It there is a rough sea I have to be paddling for hours on end and balancing the thing too.��� It all lies in balancing it.��� Food I carry, tinned food and water in bottles.��� Sometimes I carry tender coconuts also - and lots of quinine

properties.name: Cox's Bazar
properties.desc: Cox's Bazar District, Chittagong Division, Bangladesh

properties.name: Rangoon (Yangon)
properties.quote: After my arrival in Rangoon, with the south west monsoon soon to set in, I tried to get in touch with one of the small Burmese movie production houses in order to be able to make documentaries of the beautiful river areas during the monsoon. Unfortunately, I only ever got as far as hearing the friendly Burmese explain to me repeatedly that their people had no interest in cultural films and the only films with an audience in Burma were love stories. Since I hardly fit the picture of a Burmese Casanova, I was forced to continue my journey from Rangoon to Penang during the monsoon.

properties.name: Mergui (Myeik)
properties.quote: During my time on the Mergui Archipelago the monsoon suddenly started to blow. Those thunderstorms that suddenly speared out of nowhere, combined with gale force winds which simply blew my boat along for miles, improved my confidence in my little boat and provided me with many adventures.

properties.name: Singapore
properties.quote: A new kayak was waiting for me at Singapore. I transferred my luggage, and set out for Sumatra

properties.name: Muntok (Mentok)
properties.desc: Mentok, West Bangka Regency, Bangka Belitung Islands, Indonesia

properties.name: Batavia (Jakarta)
properties.desc: Jakarta, Gambir, Jakarta Special Capital Region, Indonesia

properties.name: Jepara
properties.quote: Weather good and I got as far as just short of Japera. Entered a wrong bay by mistake. Slept in the boat. Beautiful sunset. The next morning I went across to Japera. Mouth of the river rather difficult to pass.

properties.name: Pulau Mandalika
properties.quote: Now had to go to Pulau Mandalika. Good weather and arrived at Mandalika at 4 o'clock. Went to the guard at the lighthouse to fetch drinking water.���People very friendly. Slept in the boat. Lots of rain overnight. Bad weather. Strong winds and can't continue. Went back to the guard at the lighthouse and slept there. Weather gets stormier. Strong rain.

properties.name: Surabaya
properties.desc: Surabaya, Alun-Alun Contong, East Java, Indonesia

properties.name: Lombok
properties.quote: When in North Bali I again had a severe bout of malaria, and before I was more than half-way better I foolishly decided to try to reach Lombok. There was a strong current against me for most of that leg of the trip, and before I reached land malaria had the upper hand again and I was a miserable, shivering victim in its clutch.��� Some natives came down to the beach and half-carried me up to the village, where the Kepala Kampong (village chief) received me

properties.name: Soembawa (Sumbawa)
properties.desc: Sumbawa Besar, West Nusa Tenggara, Indonesia

properties.name: Flores
properties.desc: Golo Ndari, East Nusa Tenggara, Indonesia

properties.name: Maomere (Maumere)
properties.desc: Maumere, Kota Uneng, Alok, Kabupaten Sikka, Nusa Tenggara Tim., Indonesia

properties.name: Larantoeka (Larantuka)
properties.desc: Larantuka, East Flores Regency, East Nusa Tenggara, Indonesia

properties.desc: Adonara, East Flores Regency, East Nusa Tenggara, Indonesia

properties.name: Lamakera
properties.desc: Lamakera, Watobuku, Solor Tim., Kabupaten Flores Timur, Nusa Tenggara Tim., Indonesia

properties.name: Lomblen (Lembata)
properties.desc: Lembata, Katakeja, Atadei, Lembata Regency, East Nusa Tenggara, Indonesia

properties.name: Kalabahi
properties.desc: Kalabahi Tengah, East Nusa Tenggara, Indonesia

properties.name: Kisar
properties.desc: Kisar, Maluku Barat Daya Regency, Maluku, Indonesia

properties.name: Vanimo
properties.desc: Vanimo District, Sandaun, Papua New Guinea

properties.name: Madang
properties.desc: Madang, Madang District, Madang,  Papua New Guinea

properties.name: Lae
properties.desc: Lae, Morobe Province, Papua New Guinea

properties.name: Lababia Island
properties.desc: Mumeng District, Morobe Province,  Papua New Guinea

properties.name: Zaka
properties.desc: Zaka, Morobe Province, Papua New Guinea

properties.name: Kerema
properties.desc: Kerema, Kerema District, Gulf, Papua New Guinea

properties.name: Daru Island
properties.desc: Daru District, Western, Papua New Guinea
properties.quote: In the early morning of 5 September 1939 he arrived at Daru, the exit port of Papua.  The next landing was to be Australia.  An old fisherman approached Speck and said to him: ?Congratulations on your landing in Daru, ? unfortunately I have bad news for you, -  war has broken out!?

properties.name: Saibai Island
properties.desc: Saibai Island, Torres Strait, Queensland, Australia
properties.quote: Three Australian police were waiting for him to berth his kayak. If this was the German invasion, these cops could handle it. "Well done, feller!'' they said, shaking his hand warmly.������"You've made it ? Germany to Australia in THAT.��� But now we've got a piece of bad news for you.��� You are an enemy alien.��� We are going to intern you." They did just that.

properties.name: Melbourne
properties.quote: Identified by 2 mobile traffic police while he was wheeling a new bicycle up a hill in Kew, Oscar Walter Speck (36), a German internee who escaped from a Goulburn Valley internment camp on January 9, was recaptured at 5 pm today.

properties.name: Lightning Ridge
properties.desc: Lightning Ridge, New South Wales, Australia

properties.name: Killcare
properties.desc: Killcare, Central Coast, New South Wales
